1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Scene 1: The Art of Ordering in Japanese – A Beginner’s Guide

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,533
Excuse me.

3
00:00:05,556 --> 00:00:08,789
Could I see the menu, please?

4
00:00:08,812 --> 00:00:10,949
Certainly.

5
00:00:10,973 --> 00:00:14,673
Here’s our menu.

6
00:00:14,696 --> 00:00:17,430
Thank you.

7
00:00:17,453 --> 00:00:22,420
Could I also get some water?

8
00:00:22,443 --> 00:00:25,143
Of course.

9
00:00:25,166 --> 00:00:28,704
I’ll bring it right away.

10
00:00:28,728 --> 00:00:31,161
Excuse me.

11
00:00:31,184 --> 00:00:34,287
I’d like to place my order.

12
00:00:34,311 --> 00:00:36,577
Certainly.

13
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:39,434
Are you ready to order?

14
00:00:39,457 --> 00:00:43,090
I’ll have the same as that, please.

15
00:00:43,113 --> 00:00:46,346
The hamburger steak set, correct?

16
00:00:46,369 --> 00:00:48,403
Certainly.

17
00:00:48,426 --> 00:00:53,139
What do you recommend?

18
00:00:53,163 --> 00:00:57,196
Our seasonal vegetable salad is very popular.

19
00:00:57,219 --> 00:01:01,358
Then I’ll have that too, please.

20
00:01:01,382 --> 00:01:04,015
Of course.

21
00:01:04,038 --> 00:01:07,072
Where’s the restroom?

22
00:01:07,095 --> 00:01:10,595
It’s at the back over there.

23
00:01:10,618 --> 00:01:13,451
Thank you.

24
00:01:13,474 --> 00:01:16,390
Here’s your order.

25
00:01:16,413 --> 00:01:19,769
Your meal is ready.

26
00:01:19,793 --> 00:01:22,171
Excuse me.

27
00:01:22,195 --> 00:01:26,028
Could I get this to go?

28
00:01:26,051 --> 00:01:27,951
Certainly.

29
00:01:27,974 --> 00:01:31,407
I’ll bring you a takeout container.

30
00:01:31,430 --> 00:01:35,814
Could you clear these empty plates?

31
00:01:35,838 --> 00:01:37,938
Certainly.

32
00:01:37,961 --> 00:01:40,535
I’ll take those away for you.

33
00:01:40,558 --> 00:01:43,925
Could I have the bill, please?

34
00:01:43,948 --> 00:01:46,881
Please proceed to the register.

35
00:01:46,904 --> 00:01:50,638
Your total comes to 2,500 yen.

36
00:01:50,661 --> 00:01:55,601
Could my friend and I pay separately?

37
00:01:55,624 --> 00:01:57,769
Certainly.

38
00:01:57,793 --> 00:02:00,626
That’s no problem at all.

39
00:02:00,649 --> 00:02:03,649
Scene 2: Clothing Fitting & Exchange – A Shopper’s Guide

40
00:02:03,649 --> 00:02:06,182
Excuse me.

41
00:02:06,205 --> 00:02:11,143
Do you have this shirt in a different color?

42
00:02:11,167 --> 00:02:13,683
Certainly.

43
00:02:13,706 --> 00:02:18,206
We have it in white and black.

44
00:02:18,229 --> 00:02:22,823
Could I try on the black one?

45
00:02:22,847 --> 00:02:25,680
Certainly.

46
00:02:25,703 --> 00:02:30,470
The fitting rooms are over there.

47
00:02:30,493 --> 00:02:33,031
It fits perfectly!

48
00:02:33,054 --> 00:02:34,054
Could I get a brand-new one of these?

49
00:02:34,077 --> 00:02:37,511
Of course.

50
00:02:37,534 --> 00:02:41,520
Let me check our stock.

51
00:02:41,543 --> 00:02:46,090
Could you give me a little discount?

52
00:02:46,113 --> 00:02:47,113
I’m sorry,

53
00:02:47,137 --> 00:02:51,775
this item isn’t part of the sale.

54
00:02:51,798 --> 00:02:54,698
I see.

55
00:02:54,721 --> 00:02:55,721
I’ll take this, then.

56
00:02:55,744 --> 00:02:58,777
Thank you.

57
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:06,238
I’m giving this to a friend—could you wrap it as a gift?

58
00:03:06,261 --> 00:03:07,261
Of course.

59
00:03:07,284 --> 00:03:08,284
Would our free gift wrapping be okay?

60
00:03:08,308 --> 00:03:12,008
Yes, please.

61
00:03:12,031 --> 00:03:16,505
Would you like a plastic bag?

62
00:03:16,528 --> 00:03:17,528
No, I have an eco-bag, thanks.

63
00:03:17,551 --> 00:03:22,518
How would you like to pay?

64
00:03:22,541 --> 00:03:26,500
Do you accept credit cards?

65
00:03:26,523 --> 00:03:27,523
Of course.

66
00:03:27,546 --> 00:03:30,813
Now available for your use.

67
00:03:30,836 --> 00:03:36,569
Can I return it if the size doesn’t fit?

68
00:03:36,592 --> 00:03:37,592
Yes, you can return it within a week if you have the receipt.

69
00:03:37,615 --> 00:03:40,615
Scene 3: Navigating Traffic and Customer Requests

70
00:03:40,615 --> 00:03:43,054
Excuse me,

71
00:03:43,078 --> 00:03:47,111
to Tokyo Station, please.

72
00:03:47,134 --> 00:03:49,968
Of course.

73
00:03:49,991 --> 00:03:50,991
Which exit at Tokyo Station?

74
00:03:51,014 --> 00:03:54,931
Yaesu Exit, please.

75
00:03:54,955 --> 00:03:58,821
Alright, we’re on our way.

76
00:03:58,844 --> 00:04:02,711
The roads are pretty congested, huh?

77
00:04:02,734 --> 00:04:03,734
Yeah,

78
00:04:03,757 --> 00:04:07,862
it’s always busy around this time in the evening.

79
00:04:07,885 --> 00:04:08,885
I’m in a hurry, so could you take a faster route?

80
00:04:08,908 --> 00:04:11,463
I see.

81
00:04:11,487 --> 00:04:15,263
Shall I take an alternate route?

82
00:04:15,286 --> 00:04:18,519
Yes, please.

83
00:04:18,542 --> 00:04:19,542
We’ll be there in about five minutes.

84
00:04:19,566 --> 00:04:22,364
Thank you.

85
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:23,387
Oh, please stop in front of that convenience store.

86
00:04:23,410 --> 00:04:25,881
Here we are.

87
00:04:25,905 --> 00:04:26,905
That’ll be 2,000 yen.

88
00:04:26,928 --> 00:04:27,928
Can I pay with a transit IC card?

89
00:04:27,951 --> 00:04:32,218
Yes, please tap it here.

90
00:04:32,241 --> 00:04:35,756
May I have a receipt, please?

91
00:04:35,779 --> 00:04:39,448
Here you go.

92
00:04:39,471 --> 00:04:42,783
Please be mindful of your belongings.

93
00:04:42,806 --> 00:04:43,806
Excuse me,

94
00:04:43,830 --> 00:04:44,830
I have a lot of luggage—could you open the trunk for me?

95
00:04:44,853 --> 00:04:48,720
Sure, I’ll open it right now.

96
00:04:48,743 --> 00:04:51,243
Thank you very much.

97
00:04:51,265 --> 00:04:52,265
Take care on your way.

98
00:04:52,289 --> 00:04:55,289
Scene 4: Hotel Check-In Process

99
00:04:55,289 --> 00:04:57,789
Excuse me.

100
00:04:57,812 --> 00:05:01,445
I’d like to check in, please.

101
00:05:01,468 --> 00:05:03,643
Certainly.

102
00:05:03,667 --> 00:05:08,334
May I have the name on your reservation?

103
00:05:08,357 --> 00:05:11,116
Smith.

104
00:05:11,139 --> 00:05:14,481
I’ll be staying for three nights.

105
00:05:14,504 --> 00:05:17,460
Mr. Smith, correct?

106
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:21,617
Please sign here.

107
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:28,015
Could you hold my luggage before I go to the room?

108
00:05:28,038 --> 00:05:30,772
Of course.

109
00:05:30,794 --> 00:05:34,228
We’ll take care of it for you.

110
00:05:34,251 --> 00:05:39,924
Excuse me, could you tell me the Wi-Fi password?

111
00:05:39,948 --> 00:05:43,931
It’s written on the back of your room key.

112
00:05:43,954 --> 00:05:46,787
Thank you.

113
00:05:46,810 --> 00:05:50,959
What time does breakfast start?

114
00:05:50,982 --> 00:05:57,139
Breakfast is served from 7 AM in the restaurant on the first floor.

115
00:05:57,162 --> 00:06:00,029
I see.

116
00:06:00,052 --> 00:06:03,202
Your room is on the fifth floor.

117
00:06:03,226 --> 00:06:05,770
Excuse me.

118
00:06:05,793 --> 00:06:09,126
The hot water isn’t working in my room.

119
00:06:09,149 --> 00:06:12,317
We apologize for the inconvenience.

120
00:06:12,340 --> 00:06:15,925
We’ll check it right away.

121
00:06:15,949 --> 00:06:20,616
Also, could I get an extra towel?

122
00:06:20,638 --> 00:06:23,472
Of course.

123
00:06:23,495 --> 00:06:26,264
I’ll bring one to your room.

124
00:06:26,287 --> 00:06:32,987
If the hot water isn’t fixed, could I change rooms?

125
00:06:33,010 --> 00:06:36,925
Yes, of course.

126
00:06:36,949 --> 00:06:41,708
Could you call a taxi for me tomorrow morning?

127
00:06:41,731 --> 00:06:44,365
Of course.

128
00:06:44,389 --> 00:06:47,582
What time will you be departing?

129
00:06:47,606 --> 00:06:51,382
Let's meet at 8 o'clock.

130
00:06:51,405 --> 00:06:54,405
Scene 5: Mastering Basic Daily Conversations in Japanese

131
00:06:54,405 --> 00:06:57,746
Excuse me, senior.

132
00:06:57,770 --> 00:07:01,645
Do you have a moment now?

133
00:07:01,668 --> 00:07:05,812
Yes, what's up?

134
00:07:05,835 --> 00:07:10,809
I forgot my pen. Could you lend me one?

135
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:15,333
Here you go. Please use this.

136
00:07:15,356 --> 00:07:18,023
Thank you.

137
00:07:18,046 --> 00:07:23,279
I don't understand how to fill out this document.

138
00:07:23,302 --> 00:07:28,136
You write your name and address here.

139
00:07:28,159 --> 00:07:33,276
Sorry, I couldn't catch that. You were speaking too fast.

140
00:07:33,299 --> 00:07:36,766
Could you say that again?

141
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:42,357
Please write your name and address here.

142
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:45,114
Thank you.

143
00:07:45,137 --> 00:07:49,814
Could you speak a little slower?

144
00:07:49,837 --> 00:07:54,424
I'm sorry. I'll be more careful.

145
00:07:54,448 --> 00:07:57,000
I've finished writing.

146
00:07:57,023 --> 00:08:00,598
What should I do next?

147
00:08:00,621 --> 00:08:04,495
Please make a copy of this.

148
00:08:04,519 --> 00:08:09,064
Could you show me how to use the copier?

149
00:08:09,087 --> 00:08:13,067
Just press this button.

150
00:08:13,091 --> 00:08:15,443
I see.

151
00:08:15,466 --> 00:08:20,499
Oh, the printing stopped.

152
00:08:20,522 --> 00:08:24,089
Could you help me with this?

153
00:08:24,113 --> 00:08:27,868
Maybe the paper is jammed.

154
00:08:27,892 --> 00:08:31,037
Please wait a moment.

155
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:34,033
You saved me!

156
00:08:34,057 --> 00:08:37,390
Thank you so much!

157
00:08:37,413 --> 00:08:42,530
You're welcome. Is there anything else you don't understand?

158
00:08:42,554 --> 00:08:46,335
I'm good for now.

159
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:50,826
Um, is it okay if I take a day off tomorrow?

160
00:08:50,849 --> 00:08:56,356
Oh, but we have an important meeting tomorrow.

161
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:59,380
Scene 6: Capturing Moments – Photography and Permission in Conversation

162
00:08:59,380 --> 00:09:01,928
Excuse me.

163
00:09:01,951 --> 00:09:06,534
Could you take a photo for me?

164
00:09:06,558 --> 00:09:10,355
Sure, I'd be happy to.

165
00:09:10,378 --> 00:09:13,745
Could you lend me your camera?

166
00:09:13,768 --> 00:09:17,753
Just press this button.

167
00:09:17,777 --> 00:09:20,158
Certainly.

168
00:09:20,181 --> 00:09:23,348
Cheese!

169
00:09:23,372 --> 00:09:27,451
Shall we take one more?

170
00:09:27,474 --> 00:09:30,049
Thank you.

171
00:09:30,073 --> 00:09:35,206
Would it be okay if we took a photo together?

172
00:09:35,229 --> 00:09:38,422
With me?

173
00:09:38,446 --> 00:09:42,512
Yes, I'd love to!

174
00:09:42,535 --> 00:09:45,969
This will be a great keepsake.

175
00:09:45,992 --> 00:09:51,512
Excuse me, is it okay to go inside the castle?

176
00:09:51,535 --> 00:09:56,108
You need a ticket to enter there.

177
00:09:56,131 --> 00:10:00,165
Where can I buy a ticket?

178
00:10:00,188 --> 00:10:05,093
You can buy one at that white building over there.

179
00:10:05,116 --> 00:10:09,434
Do you have an English pamphlet?

180
00:10:09,457 --> 00:10:12,957
You can get one at the reception desk.

181
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:17,332
Do you offer Japanese guided tours?

182
00:10:17,356 --> 00:10:21,822
There's a free tour starting at 10 o'clock.

183
00:10:21,845 --> 00:10:25,412
I'd like to join.

184
00:10:25,435 --> 00:10:31,303
My luggage is heavy. Are there any lockers available?

185
00:10:31,327 --> 00:10:35,560
It's near the station.

186
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:39,766
How late are you open until?

187
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:43,157
Until 5 PM.

188
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:45,857
I see.

189
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:50,813
Can I eat my lunch on the bench?

190
00:10:50,836 --> 00:10:53,136
Certainly.

191
00:10:53,159 --> 00:10:56,992
Feel free to eat or drink here.

192
00:10:57,015 --> 00:11:00,015
Scene 7: Finding a Clinic and Describing Symptoms

193
00:11:00,015 --> 00:11:02,720
Excuse me.

194
00:11:02,743 --> 00:11:07,043
Could you tell me where the nearest clinic is?

195
00:11:07,066 --> 00:11:09,933
What seems to be the problem?

196
00:11:09,957 --> 00:11:13,635
You don’t look well.

197
00:11:13,658 --> 00:11:18,092
I’ve had a headache since yesterday.

198
00:11:18,115 --> 00:11:21,233
Do you have a fever as well?

199
00:11:21,256 --> 00:11:25,638
Yes, I have a slight fever.

200
00:11:25,662 --> 00:11:29,095
That sounds serious.

201
00:11:29,118 --> 00:11:32,230
An internal medicine clinic would be best.

202
00:11:32,254 --> 00:11:36,921
Is there a doctor who speaks English?

203
00:11:36,944 --> 00:11:42,112
The clinic near the station should have English-speaking staff.

204
00:11:42,135 --> 00:11:44,841
Thank you.

205
00:11:44,864 --> 00:11:48,097
I’ll try going there.

206
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:51,075
Please take care.

207
00:11:51,099 --> 00:11:53,766
Excuse me.

208
00:11:53,789 --> 00:11:56,822
Could I get examined?

209
00:11:56,845 --> 00:11:59,482
Is this your first visit?

210
00:11:59,506 --> 00:12:03,039
May I see your insurance card?

211
00:12:03,062 --> 00:12:07,129
Can I use my Japanese health insurance?

212
00:12:07,152 --> 00:12:10,618
Yes, you can.

213
00:12:10,641 --> 00:12:13,880
Please fill out this medical questionnaire.

214
00:12:13,903 --> 00:12:19,237
I’m not feeling well. Could I rest for a bit?

215
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:23,244
Please lie down on this bed.

216
00:12:23,267 --> 00:12:30,100
Doctor, I need to take off work. Could you write me a medical certificate?

217
00:12:30,123 --> 00:12:32,390
I see.

218
00:12:32,413 --> 00:12:35,772
I’ll prescribe some medication for you.

219
00:12:35,796 --> 00:12:39,671
Could I get something for the pain?

220
00:12:39,694 --> 00:12:43,796
Please take this after every meal.

221
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:46,453
Take care and get well soon.

222
00:12:46,476 --> 00:12:49,643
Thank you very much.

223
00:12:49,666 --> 00:12:52,666
Scene 8: What to Do When Your Bag Is Stolen

224
00:12:52,666 --> 00:12:56,536
Excuse me, please help me!

225
00:12:56,559 --> 00:12:57,559
What seems to be the problem?

226
00:12:57,582 --> 00:13:00,249
Please stay calm.

227
00:13:00,272 --> 00:13:04,505
My bag was stolen.

228
00:13:04,528 --> 00:13:05,528
What?!

229
00:13:05,552 --> 00:13:08,785
That’s terrible!

230
00:13:08,808 --> 00:13:09,808
We should call the police right away.

231
00:13:09,831 --> 00:13:14,164
My phone was in the bag too.

232
00:13:14,187 --> 00:13:17,487
Could I borrow your phone?

233
00:13:17,510 --> 00:13:21,344
Here you go.

234
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:22,367
It’s 110 for the police.

235
00:13:22,390 --> 00:13:27,423
Hello, my bag was stolen.

236
00:13:27,446 --> 00:13:30,746
The police, right?

237
00:13:30,769 --> 00:13:31,769
Where did it happen?

238
00:13:31,792 --> 00:13:32,792
I left it in the station restroom and when I came back, it was gone.

239
00:13:32,816 --> 00:13:33,816
What was inside the bag?

240
00:13:33,839 --> 00:13:38,552
My wallet and passport.

241
00:13:38,575 --> 00:13:39,575
Was there a credit card in it?

242
00:13:39,598 --> 00:13:40,598
Yes. I need to cancel it immediately.

243
00:13:40,622 --> 00:13:46,591
You’ll need to contact the card company yourself to cancel it.

244
00:13:46,614 --> 00:13:49,559
I see.

245
00:13:49,582 --> 00:13:50,582
Also, where is the Japanese embassy?

246
00:13:50,606 --> 00:13:55,395
You need to get your passport reissued, right?

247
00:13:55,418 --> 00:13:58,851
I'll give you a map.

248
00:13:58,874 --> 00:13:59,874
My house keys are in my bag, and I can't get into my room.

249
00:13:59,898 --> 00:14:00,898
Could you give me the landlord's contact information?

250
00:14:00,921 --> 00:14:01,921
I don’t have my phone, so I don’t know the number.

251
00:14:01,944 --> 00:14:05,286
This is tough, isn’t it?

252
00:14:05,309 --> 00:14:09,107
Could I call my family?

253
00:14:09,131 --> 00:14:14,466
Yes, please use this phone.

254
00:14:14,489 --> 00:14:17,489
Scene 9: Making Plans with Friends

255
00:14:17,489 --> 00:14:23,756
Hey, let’s go out together next weekend!

256
00:14:23,779 --> 00:14:26,018
Sounds good!

257
00:14:26,041 --> 00:14:27,041
Where should we go?

258
00:14:27,064 --> 00:14:28,064
There’s a new café I want to check out.

259
00:14:28,087 --> 00:14:30,721
Got it.

260
00:14:30,744 --> 00:14:31,744
So, give me your LINE ID.

261
00:14:31,767 --> 00:14:32,767
Sure,

262
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:37,058
Scan this QR code.

263
00:14:37,082 --> 00:14:40,115
I added you!

264
00:14:40,138 --> 00:14:43,675
I’ll send you the details later.

265
00:14:43,699 --> 00:14:44,699
Sorry,

266
00:14:44,722 --> 00:14:45,722
Wait a sec.

267
00:14:45,745 --> 00:14:49,379
I can’t tie my shoelaces.

268
00:14:49,402 --> 00:14:52,735
Take your time.

269
00:14:52,758 --> 00:14:56,391
I’m thirsty.

270
00:14:56,414 --> 00:14:57,414
Can we stop by a convenience store?

271
00:14:57,438 --> 00:15:00,188
Yeah.

272
00:15:00,211 --> 00:15:05,200
Oh, and could you lend me some money too?

273
00:15:05,223 --> 00:15:06,223
How much?

274
00:15:06,246 --> 00:15:07,246
Just 500 yen.

275
00:15:07,269 --> 00:15:11,028
I forgot my wallet.

276
00:15:11,052 --> 00:15:13,885
You’re hopeless.

277
00:15:13,908 --> 00:15:14,908
Here’s 500 yen.

278
00:15:14,931 --> 00:15:17,365
Thanks!

279
00:15:17,388 --> 00:15:21,374
I’ll pay you back tomorrow for sure.

280
00:15:21,397 --> 00:15:22,397
This cake is amazing!

281
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:23,421
Really?

282
00:15:23,444 --> 00:15:24,444
Can I have a bite?

283
00:15:24,467 --> 00:15:27,062
Sure.

284
00:15:27,085 --> 00:15:30,352
Here, say 'ah'.

285
00:15:30,375 --> 00:15:31,375
Wow, it’s delicious!

286
00:15:31,398 --> 00:15:32,398
Want to try my pancake too?

287
00:15:32,421 --> 00:15:33,421
Yes! Oh, send me a photo.

288
00:15:33,445 --> 00:15:35,843
Yeah.

289
00:15:35,866 --> 00:15:39,370
I just sent it on LINE.

290
00:15:39,393 --> 00:15:41,659
Thanks!

291
00:15:41,682 --> 00:15:42,682
Let’s keep this place a secret from everyone else.

292
00:15:42,706 --> 00:15:44,972
Got it.

293
00:15:44,995 --> 00:15:48,562
Our little secret, got it.

294
00:15:48,585 --> 00:15:51,585
Scene 10: Preparing and Confirming for a Meeting

295
00:15:51,585 --> 00:15:54,618
Good work today.

296
00:15:54,641 --> 00:15:57,908
Can you hear me?

297
00:15:57,931 --> 00:16:01,690
Yes, I can hear you.

298
00:16:01,713 --> 00:16:03,904
Excuse me,

299
00:16:03,928 --> 00:16:07,647
Please turn on your microphone.

300
00:16:07,670 --> 00:16:10,737
Oh, sorry about that.

301
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:13,919
I just turned it on.

302
00:16:13,943 --> 00:16:17,009
No problem.

303
00:16:17,032 --> 00:16:20,999
Let’s get this meeting started.

304
00:16:21,022 --> 00:16:26,089
Take a look at this week’s sales data.

305
00:16:26,112 --> 00:16:31,101
Could you share your screen, please?

306
00:16:31,124 --> 00:16:35,163
Sure, just a moment.

307
00:16:35,187 --> 00:16:38,420
How about now?

308
00:16:38,443 --> 00:16:42,276
I still can’t see it.

309
00:16:42,299 --> 00:16:46,937
Would it help if I reconnected?

310
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:49,694
I see.

311
00:16:49,717 --> 00:16:52,386
I’ll wait.

312
00:16:52,409 --> 00:16:55,275
Thanks for your patience.

313
00:16:55,298 --> 00:17:00,565
Your voice sounds a little faint.

314
00:17:00,588 --> 00:17:03,255
Really?

315
00:17:03,278 --> 00:17:08,657
Could you speak up a bit?

316
00:17:08,681 --> 00:17:12,416
Testing my mic now.

317
00:17:12,439 --> 00:17:14,814
How’s this?

318
00:17:14,838 --> 00:17:19,551
Perfect, I can hear you clearly now.

319
00:17:19,575 --> 00:17:22,342
Great!

320
00:17:22,365 --> 00:17:26,964
Is it okay if I record this meeting?

321
00:17:26,987 --> 00:17:31,258
Yes, that’s fine.

322
00:17:31,281 --> 00:17:36,619
Please share any important URLs in the chat.

323
00:17:36,643 --> 00:17:40,914
I just sent the link.

324
00:17:40,937 --> 00:17:43,970
Got it.

325
00:17:43,993 --> 00:17:48,775
Please email me the details later.

326
00:17:48,798 --> 00:17:51,732
Understood.

327
00:17:51,755 --> 00:17:56,488
I’ll send the meeting minutes along with it.

328
00:17:56,511 --> 00:17:59,544
Thank you.